	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-06T07:37:46">North Atlantic Smaller Companies Investment Trust plc (NASCIT) is a United Kingdom-based company engaged in portfolio investment. The Company's objective is to provide capital appreciation to its Shareholders through investing in a portfolio of smaller companies which are based primarily in countries bordering the North Atlantic Ocean. NASCIT invests in companies, both quoted and unquoted, on both sides of the Atlantic in accordance with its objective and investment policy. The Company invests in sectors, such as investment companies; construction and materials; healthcare, equipment and services; real estate; travel and leisure; general financials; support services; media; software; general industrials; industrial engineering; financial services; manufacturing, and technology hardware and equipment.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-17T03:29:54">BRIEF: For the six months ended 31 July 2015, North Atlantic Smaller Cos Inv Tr PLC revenues increased from L12.2M to L41.6M. Net income increased from L10.1M to L38.7M. Revenues reflect Financial asset at fair value increase from L11.4M to L40.4M, Income increase of 49% to L1.3M, Foreign exchange (losses)/gains) increase of 41% to -L70K. Net income benefited from Stock based remuneration decrease of 96% to L7K (expense).</Text>
